# Official documentation first

Before changing components, styles, routing, or native behavior, consult:

- Ionic: https://ionicframework.com/docs
- Angular: https://angular.dev
- Capacitor: https://capacitorjs.com/docs

Project guide: `docs/development-guidelines.md`

## Ionic styling (required)

1. Use documented **component APIs** (`color`, `outline`, `fill`, `disabled`) before custom CSS.
2. Theme with **documented CSS custom properties** only (e.g. `ion-chip`: `--background`, `--color`).
3. Do **not** nest `ion-label` inside `ion-chip` — use plain text per ion-chip docs.
4. Avoid global `ion-*` overrides; prefer page-scoped `*.page.scss` or design tokens.
5. Horizontal `ion-chip` rows: `flex-shrink: 0` on each chip to prevent truncated text.

## Examples

```html
<!-- BAD - ion-label inside chip, custom class fighting Ionic -->
<ion-chip class="my-chip" outline>
  <ion-label>Fire</ion-label>
</ion-chip>

<!-- GOOD - Ionic API + plain text -->
<ion-chip color="primary">Fire</ion-chip>
<ion-chip outline>Water</ion-chip>
```

```scss
/* BAD - undocumented host hacks */
ion-chip.my-chip {
  width: 12px;
  border: 1px solid gray;
}

/* GOOD - documented CSS variables */
ion-chip {
  --background: var(--jublia-color-surface);
  --color: var(--jublia-color-text);
}
```
